              "free_txt": [
                " Recoiled reaction products were momentum",
                "analyzed in series of magnetic dipoles and",
                "quadrupoles and electrostatic dipoles. Recoils were",
                "identified in focal plane detector"
              ]
            },
            {
              "x4_code": "(IOCH)",
              "free_txt": [
                " Ionization chamber is a 25 cm long isobutane-",
                "filled volume separated from the beam line by a thin",
                "Mylar window. The anode of the chamber is divided",
                "into three segments, providing additional energy loss",
                "information for recoil identification. The first",
                "segment provides the primary energy loss measurement,",
                "while the total energy is obtained from the sum of",
                "all three ion chamber segments."
              ]
            },
            {
              "x4_code": "(BGO)",
              "free_txt": [
                " The target was surrounded by an array of thirty",
                "hexagonal BGO detectors arranged in close-packed",
                "geometry. The gamma rays detected by the BGO crystals",
                "provide a timing signal for the separator time of",
                "flight."
              ]
            },
            {
              "x4_code": "(MCPLT)",
              "free_txt": [
                " To further increase the beam suppression",
                "through improved particle identification a local",
                "time-of-flight system was used. The system consisted",
                "of two timing detectors, each of which consists of a",
                "carbon foil, an electrostatic mirror and a",
                "microchannel plate."
              ]
            }
